From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Werner <werner@armbian.com>
Date: Tue, 26 Mar 2026 04:45:12 +0000
Subject: Fix compilation of uwe5622 in Linux 7.1

Kernel 7.1 removed legacy GPIO and cfg80211 APIs:
- Replace of_gpio.h with gpio/consumer.h and of.h
- Migrate from integer GPIO to GPIO descriptor API
  - of_get_named_gpio() -> devm_gpiod_get_optional() / fwnode_gpiod_get_index()
  - gpio_is_valid() -> !IS_ERR_OR_NULL()
  - gpio_request() / gpio_free() -> automatic with devm_* API
  - gpio_direction_output() -> gpiod_set_value()
  - gpio_to_irq() -> gpiod_to_irq()
- Update cfg80211 ops: net_device* -> wireless_dev*
  - add_key, del_key, add_station, del_station, change_station, get_station
  - cfg80211_new_sta(), cfg80211_del_sta() now take wireless_dev*

Signed-off-by: Werner <werner@armbian.com>
